 value of this property is ","type":"text"},{"code":"YES","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and the map is tilted, the annotation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view appears smaller if it is towards the top of the view (closer to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"horizon) and larger if it is towards the bottom of the view (closer to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"viewpoint). This is also the behavior of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationImage","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" objects. When the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"value of this property is ","type":"text"},{"code":"NO","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or the map’s pitch is zero, the annotation view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"remains the same size regardless of its position on-screen.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default value of this property is ","type":"text"},{"code":"NO","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Keep this property set to ","type":"text"},{"code":"NO","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the view’s legibility is important.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scaling many on-screen annotation views can contribute to poor map"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"performance. Consider keeping this property disabled if your use case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"involves hundreds or thousands of annotation views."}]}],"style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","title":"MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/scalesWithViewingDistance":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"scalesWithViewingDistance"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A Boolean value that determines whether the annotation view grows and shrinks","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as the distance between the viewpoint and the annotation view changes on a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tilted map.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/scaleswithviewingdistance","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/scalesWithViewingDistance","kind":"symbol","title":"scalesWithViewingDistance","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"title":"MLNAnnotation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the visual representation of 